    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but there is no \"rediscovering\" anything. you can't build a house on a crater. when everyone knows who you really are now—the scandal, the failure—there's no dignity left to find. it just feels like the world has already moved on and decided i don't belong in it anymore. it would be so much easier to just stop fighting the weight.",
